Preheat your oven to 180°C. Fill and boil your #kettle{}. Halve, peel and chop the @onion{1} into small pieces. Peel and grate the @garlic{1%clove} (or use a #garlic press{}). Trim the bottom 2cm from the @asparagus{100%g} and pop on a #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @olive oil{1%tbsp} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Set aside.

Halve the @baby plum tomatoes{125%g}. Pop the @cider vinegar{15%ml}, @honey{15%g} and olive oil into a #medium sized bowl{}. Season with salt and pepper and mix together. Add the tomatoes, mix and set aside. Drain the @mozzarella{1} and tear into small pieces.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a #large saucepan{} on medium-high heat. Add the onion and @chorizo{90%g}(diced) and cook, stirring frequently until the chorizo is crispy and the onion is softened, ~{5-6%minutes}, then add the garlic and @sun-dried tomato paste{25%g}. Stir continuously and cook for ~{1%minute}. Stir the @orzo{180%g} into the pan followed by the @water{450%ml} and the @vegetable stock powder{1}.

> Step 3 MOD: If you've added chorizo to your meal, add it to the pan when you add the onion in the step above and
> cook along with the onion until the chorizo is crispy and the onion is softened, 5-6 mins. Continue with the rest of
> the recipe as instructed.

Bring to a simmer, stirring to combine, then reduce the heat to medium-low and simmer until the orzo is cooked and the liquid absorbed, ~{10-12%minutes}. Stir every couple of mins to ensure the orzo is not sticking to the bottom of the pan. If the mixture is looking a bit dry and the orzo is not quite cooked, just add a splash of water and keep cooking.

Meanwhile, roast the asparagus on the top shelf of your oven until tender, ~{10-12%minutes}. Once the orzo is cooked, remove from the heat. Stir in the @grated hard Italian style cheese{40%g} until melted. Taste and add salt and pepper if you feel it needs it. Add the mozzarella to the salsa and stir to combine.

Serve the orzo in #bowls{} with the roasted asparagus on one side and the tomato salsa on the other side. Enjoy!